In this module we'll learn how to package a piece of work behind a name so we can reuse it — these are called functions. We'll see how to pass values in as parameters, send a result back out with return, and give an argument a sensible default. We'll learn why variables created inside a function stay private to it — the rules around this are called scope — and figure out when to split one big function into several smaller ones. We'll put those ideas together into a Fitness Tracker Dashboard that calculates BMI, daily calorie needs, and a workout streak, each implemented behind its own function.